UML:TaggedValue.value: Collection of utilities that have not attained formal governance status, though in some cases they are on a standardization track. These are recommended best practice within the HollowWorld modelling framework.
These profiles are extensions of OGC or ISO standard models.
These profiles are extensions of OGC or ISO standard models.

Extensions to ISO 19107 Spatial Schema (implemented as GML Geometry schema), primarily dealing with simplified representations of some simple solids, surfaces and curves.
Documented in OGC 07-001

Extensions to ISO 19123 CV packages, primarily adding some additional specializations of Discrete Coverages, and also some "compact" encoded versions.
Documented in OGC 06-188r1 and corrigenda OGC 07-130, 07-155

Extensions to ISO 19107 Spatial Schema (implemented as GML Geometry schema), primarily dealing with simplified representations of some simple solids, surfaces and curves.
Documented in OGC 07-001
A subset of the 3D geometries from the gml:_Solid substitution group, not including CompositeSolid, and adding the XMML SimpleSolid group
A subset of the 1D geometries from the gml:_Curve substitution group, not including CompositeCurve, and adding the simplified XMML LineByVector
A subset of the 2D geometries from the gml:AbstractSurface substitution group.
A subset of the 2D geometries from the gml:_Surface substitution group, not including CompositeSurface, and adding the simplified XMML PlaneByVector

Extensions to ISO 19123 CV packages, primarily adding some additional specializations of Discrete Coverages, and also some "compact" encoded versions.
Documented in OGC 06-188r1 and corrigenda OGC 07-130, 07-155

Proposed additional specializations of CV_DiscreteCoverage.
CV_DiscreteCoverage is a subclass of CV_Coverage that returns a single record of values for any direct position within a single geometric object in its spatiotemporal domain.

Proposed additional specializations of CV_DiscreteCoverage.
CV_DiscreteCoverage is a subclass of CV_Coverage that returns a single record of values for any direct position within a single geometric object in its spatiotemporal domain.

The operation evaluate shall accept a DirectPosition as input and return the record of attribute values for that direct position. The data type Record is defined in ISO 19103. If the direct position passed is not in the spatiotemporal domain, then an error message shall be generated

The operation "evaluateInverse" shall accept a Record of values as input and return a set of CV_DomainObjects. Normally, this will be the set of CV_DomainObjects in the Domain that are associated with values equal to those in the input Record. However, the operation may return other CV_DomainObjects derived from those in the Domain, as specified by the application schema.
Not strictly a Coverage according to the definition in ISO 19123, since the domain objects are not geometrys.

The operation evaluate shall accept a DirectPosition as input and return the record of attribute values for that direct position. The data type Record is defined in ISO 19103. If the direct position passed is not in the spatiotemporal domain, then an error message shall be generated

The operation "evaluateInverse" shall accept a Record of values as input and return a set of CV_DomainObjects. Normally, this will be the set of CV_DomainObjects in the Domain that are associated with values equal to those in the input Record. However, the operation may return other CV_DomainObjects derived from those in the Domain, as specified by the application schema.
